  "category_subtitle": "Learn how to count pairs or teams in Japanese using 組",
  "category_detail": "<b>Counting Pairs in Japanese</b><br><br>In Japanese, the counter <b>「組」(くみ / kumi)</b> is used to count pairs, teams, or groups of people working together.<br><br>This counter is commonly used in schools, competitions, events, and when talking about couples or teams.<br><br><b>Basic Pattern</b><br>Most numbers follow the pattern:<br><span class=\"example\">number + 組</span><br><br>Examples:<br><span class=\"example\">一組</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ひとくみ / hitokumi)</span><br><span class=\"example\">二組</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ふたくみ / futakumi)</span><br><span class=\"example\">三組</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(さんくみ / sankumi)</span><br><br><b>Common Usage</b><br><span class=\"example\">三組のカップルが来ました。</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(sankumi no kappuru ga kimashita)</span><br>Meaning: Three couples came.<br><br><span class=\"example\">このクラスは五組あります。</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(kono kurasu wa gokumi arimasu)</span><br>Meaning: This class has five groups.<br><br>Compared to many other counters, the pronunciation of 組 is very regular and easy to learn.",
